This paper discusses the impact of algorithmic recommendation on the autonomy and free choice of Internet users, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several computer science sub-disciplines. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as the paper focuses on the social and cognitive effects of algorithmic recommendation. The paper also touches upon issues related to cybersecurity (cs.CY), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), information retrieval (cs.IR), and computational linguistics (cs.CL) as it discusses the biases in algorithmic recommendation and the structuring of interactions.
